<h2>Rhythm </h2>

<p>
	If you only display guitar tablatures, it might be interesting to add
	a rhythm stave to show the durations. You can do this either above or below
	the tablature.
</p>

<div id="alphaTabRhythm" data-file="/assets/files/features/Rhythm.gp5"></div>
<script type="text/javascript">
	$('#alphaTabRhythm').alphaTab({
		staves: {id: 'tab', additionalSettings: {'rhythm': true } }
	});
</script>  

<h2>Rhythm With Beams</h2>

<p>
	If you prefer beams instead of bars for single notes you can have that too. 
</p>

<div id="alphaTabRhythmBeam" data-file="/assets/files/features/Rhythm.gp5"></div>
<script type="text/javascript">
	$('#alphaTabRhythmBeam').alphaTab({
		staves: {id: 'tab', additionalSettings: {'rhythm': true, 'rhythm-beams': true } }
	});
</script>      

<h2>String Variations</h2>

<p>
	alphaTab will render tabs for stringed instruments. It takes care of 
	the number of strings and displays the tabs as you would expect.
</p>

<div id="alphaTabTabs" data-file="/assets/files/features/Tabs.gp5"></div>
<script type="text/javascript">
	$('#alphaTabTabs').alphaTab({
		staves: ['tab']
	});
</script>
